text: We ordered Chee Cheong Fun, Chwee Kway, and Yam Cake. While the base flavors were similar to those from other stalls selling similar dishes, the sauce and condiments were distinctly different. It’s a taste you either love or don’t.

Came here for breakfast on a weekday and ordered Chee Cheong Fun & Chwee Kueh. They gave me plenty of sweet sauce and  preserved radish, yet it's not very salty kind. What I like the most is the add-on crispy garlic / onion which makes the dish more flavorful!
Had the kwee kueh and chee cheong fun. The cai po nice and quite generous. Cheong fun has good texture. 1 cheong fun + 4 kwee kueh + take away box = $4.30

Bought soon kueh back. One piece was already torn when it was packed. The skin of the soon kueh is very thick and the filings  is quite little. However the taste is nice.
Also they are very generous withe the chilli and the sweet sauce. Chilli is also very nice and goes well with the soon kueh.
Friendly service, chee cheong fun is unique and delicious.  Good all day food.  My go to stall if I want a light meal.
